Shopping API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

AddBufferSkuCartItem
PATCH | Returns: bool | Path: /Shopping/CurrentCart/AddBufferSkuCartItem

Use to add the Buffer Sku in a quantity that will allow the requirements to be met in the specified session cart for the current user (Shopping, Quote, Samples)

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
BufferSkuSEOURL string body Yes Buffer Sku SEO URL
AmountToFill string body Yes Amount to Fill (will divide cost of item to get quantity to add)
TypeName string body No Cart Type Name
StoreID int? body No The identifier of the store to use, if any
FranchiseID int? body No The identifier of the franchise to use, if any
BrandID int? body No The identifier of the brand to use, if any

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AddBufferSkuCartItemDto>{
	BufferSkuSEOURL: this.someValue1, // string 
	AmountToFill: this.someValue2, // string 
	TypeName: this.someValue3, // string 
	StoreID: this.someValue4, // number? 
	FranchiseID: this.someValue5, // number? 
	BrandID: this.someValue6, // number? 
};
this.cvApi.shopping.AddBufferSkuCartItem(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

AddCartItem
POST | Returns: CEFActionResponse<Nullable`1> | Path: /Shopping/CurrentCart/Item/Add

Use to add an item to the specified session cart for the current user (Shopping, Quote, Samples)

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ProductID int body Yes The ID of the product to add
Quantity decimal body No The quantity of the product to add
SerializableAttributes SerializableAttributesDictionary body No Cart Item Serializable JSON Attributes
Targets List<SalesItemTargetBaseModel> body No Shipment to add to item
ForceUniqueLineItemKey string body No [Optional]
TypeName string body No Cart Type Name
StoreID int? body No The identifier of the store to use, if any
FranchiseID int? body No The identifier of the franchise to use, if any
BrandID int? body No The identifier of the brand to use, if any

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AddCartItemDto>{
	ProductID: this.someValue1, // number 
	Quantity: this.someValue2, // number 
	SerializableAttributes: this.someValue3, // SerializableAttributesDictionary 
	Targets: this.someValue4, // Array<SalesItemTargetBaseModel> 
	ForceUniqueLineItemKey: this.someValue5, // string 
	TypeName: this.someValue6, // string 
	StoreID: this.someValue7, // number? 
	FranchiseID: this.someValue8, // number? 
	BrandID: this.someValue9, // number? 
};
this.cvApi.shopping.AddCartItem(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

AdminUpdateCartItemQuantityForUser
PUT | Returns: CEFActionResponse<decimal> | Path: /Shopping/AdminForUser/Item/UpdateQuantity

Updates only the Quantity value for the item, overrides any previous value, not trying to adjust by offset. Returns the value supplied unless it needed to be modified for purchasing or stock limits.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
CartItemID int body Yes The identifier of the cart item to change the quantity value on.
Quantity decimal body Yes The new Quantity value to set (actual number, not an offset).
QuantityBackOrdered decimal body Yes The new Quantity Back-Ordered value to set (actual number, not an offset).
QuantityPreSold decimal body Yes The new Quantity Pre-Sold value to set (actual number, not an offset).

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AdminUpdateCartItemQuantityForUserDto>{
	CartItemID: this.someValue1, // number 
	Quantity: this.someValue2, // number 
	QuantityBackOrdered: this.someValue3, // number 
	QuantityPreSold: this.someValue4, // number 
};

		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;

AdminUpdateUserCart
PUT | Returns: CEFActionResponse | Path: /Shopping/AdminForUser/Cart/UpdateUserCart

Modifies a cart with updated data. Admins Only

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
RequestedShipDate DateTime? body No The date when a user would like to receive their products
SubtotalShippingModifier decimal? Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute

UpdateCartItemQuantity
PUT | Returns: CEFActionResponse<decimal> | Path: /Shopping/CurrentCart/Item/UpdateQuantity

Updates only the Quantity value for the item, overrides any previous value, not trying to adjust by offset. Returns the value supplied unless it needed to be modified for purchasing or stock limits.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description

QuantityPreSold decimal body Yes The new Quantity Pre-Sold value to set (actual number, not an offset).
